{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Adopt the DCO: declarative Gerrit enforcement, contributor docs, agent sign-off policy\n\n## Why\n\nrebar has no inbound-IP mechanism (no DCO, no CLA). Both external reports and peer convergence recommend DCO over CLA: Qt's CLA is the stated reason it cannot accept PRs, and OpenStack replaced its CLA with the DCO for all contributions (TC resolution 2025-05-20, https://governance.openstack.org/tc/resolutions/20250520-replace-the-cla-with-dco-for-all-contributions.html) explicitly to lower the barrier, directing enforcement into Gerrit itself — the server rejects an unsigned push at `refs/for/*` time, zero new infrastructure, before any review/CI spend. Gerrit documents `receive.requireSignedOffBy` as a per-project `project.config` key (https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/config-project-config.html#receive.requireSignedOffBy — inheritable, NOT site-only like `submitWholeTopic`); live verification below guards against placement surprises anyway.\n\n## What\n\n- **Declarative config path (never a manual push):** add `requireSignedOffBy = true` to the `[receive]` section of `infra/gerrit/project.config` and roll out via the existing `setup-project.sh` flow to `refs/meta/config` (JoeOakhartNava admin identity). Rationale: `setup-project.sh` overwrites `project.config` on every run, so a one-off manual push would be silently reverted at the next invocation.\n- **Rollback procedure (documented in the same commit):** revert the line in `infra/gerrit/project.config`, re-run `setup-project.sh` — same declarative path, one command; note this in the runbook comment beside the key.\n- **Exact sign-off trailer for agent/bot commits (decided now, not deferred):** `Signed-off-by: Joe Oakhart <joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com>` — the responsible human's real name with his registered plus-addressed mailbox (routes to the human; kernel practice accepts plus-addresses; the certifying identity is the human, satisfying DCO 1.1). \"Agent/bot commits\" is defined as: any commit authored under the RebarBotNava Gerrit identity / `joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com` committer email — one definition used consistently in all docs.\n- **Automation inventory (decision rule, not a vague sweep):** enumerate commit-creating automation with `rg -l \"git commit\" infra/ scripts/ .github/ Makefile` at execution; known consumers to update so their commits carry the trailer: `infra/gerrit/reviewbot-e2e.sh`, `infra/gerrit/feature-branch-e2e.sh`, `infra/gerrit/feature-branch-e2e-scenarios.sh` (all push to `refs/for/*` and would be rejected post-flip), plus CLAUDE.md's commit-message guidance (the committed agent guide; CLAUDE.local.md is gitignored and explicitly NOT an edit target — its guidance is mirrored from CLAUDE.md).\n- CONTRIBUTING.md \"Sign your work (DCO)\" section, moby/Docker template (https://github.com/moby/moby/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md \"Sign your work\"): link developercertificate.org, show the trailer, `git commit -s`, real-name requirement, push-time rejection note, and an Envoy-style \"fixing DCO\" note (amend/rebase re-signing). Include the shepherded-patch two-trailer rule (contributor's own sign-off required in the patch; shepherd adds theirs on amend) — coordinated with the PR-posture story's policy text.\n- This story also adds its cross-link INTO `docs/your-first-change.md` (retarget the tutorial's interim developercertificate.org link to the new CONTRIBUTING section) — ownership-inversion rule.\n- **Migration order (strict):** (1) CONTRIBUTING/CLAUDE.md/tutorial docs land; (2) e2e scripts + any inventoried automation updated — verified by running the e2e suites and grepping their created commits for the trailer; (3) server flag flipped via setup-project.sh; (4) live verification. No window where agent/bot pushes fail.\n- **Post-flip failure runbook (one paragraph in CONTRIBUTING or the config comment):** if a push is rejected for a missing trailer after enforcement is live: `git commit --amend -s --no-edit` and re-push; if agent tooling regresses, roll back the flag (procedure above) while fixing.\n- Flip GitHub's \"require sign-off on web-based commits\" on the mirror (Scope IN; one settings toggle; belt-and-braces).\n- Record the CLA decision in ADR form or the CONTRIBUTING section: none unless Nava counsel requires rights beyond Apache-2.0 §5 + DCO; escalation path = counsel review (non-blocking).\n- Peer-norm citation for the human-signs policy: Kubernetes AI-review governance (https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/github-management/ai-code-review-tools.md) — the human contributor remains fully responsible; AI is never a co-author. Cite it as supporting practice, not as the load-bearing authority (the policy stands on DCO 1.1's own terms: the certifier must be a human who can make the certification).\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: `infra/gerrit/project.config` + setup-project.sh rollout, rollback note, CONTRIBUTING.md DCO section, CLAUDE.md guidance, e2e-script trailer fixes, tutorial cross-link retarget, GitHub web-signoff toggle, live verification, CLA decision record.\nOUT: CLA machinery; the probot/dco GitHub app (acts on PR checks; PRs here are auto-closed by the lockdown workflow the PR-posture story lands — dead config for us); retrofitting existing history (DCO applies to new commits only — kernel/OpenStack precedent); CLAUDE.local.md (gitignored, not a reviewable artifact).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `infra/gerrit/project.config` contains `requireSignedOffBy = true` under `[receive]` — prove: `grep -A3 \"\\[receive\\]\" infra/gerrit/project.config` — and the change reached the server via setup-project.sh (run log recorded on the ticket).\n- [ ] Live verification recorded: an unsigned push to `refs/for/main` is rejected (capture the server message); the same commit re-pushed after `git commit --amend -s` is accepted.\n- [ ] e2e scripts create signed commits — prove: `grep -c \"commit -s\\|Signed-off-by\" infra/gerrit/reviewbot-e2e.sh infra/gerrit/feature-branch-e2e.sh infra/gerrit/feature-branch-e2e-scenarios.sh` ≥ 1 each, and one e2e suite run passes post-flip.\n- [ ] CONTRIBUTING.md DCO section present — prove: `grep -q \"developercertificate.org\" CONTRIBUTING.md` and `grep -q \"commit -s\" CONTRIBUTING.md`; includes fix-up + two-trailer shepherding rules. CLAUDE.md commit guidance names the exact bot trailer string.\n- [ ] Migration order evidenced: the ticket comments show docs+automation commits BEFORE the setup-project.sh run (timestamps/SHAs).\n- [ ] GitHub web-signoff toggle on — prove: `gh api repos/navapbc/rebar --jq .web_commit_signoff_required` = true. CLA decision recorded."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783631026244225001,"uuid":"bc252e22-b5f9-4f3b-ab37-b805b9176283"}